SIMPLE: gamy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: gamy
<hw>gam"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>Having the flavor of game, esp. of game kept
uncooked till near the condition of tainting; high-flavored.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Sporting)</fld> <def>Showing an unyielding spirit
to the last; plucky; furnishing sport; <as>as, a <ex>gamy</ex>
trout</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as <er>gamey</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>gam"i*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms></p>

<p><ent>Gan</ent>⟦br⟧
